In my recent class, I learned how coding serves as the backbone of AI and ML applications. We explored programming languages like Python, which is widely used because of its simplicity and powerful libraries such as TensorFlow, Keras, and Scikit-learn. The instructor emphasized how coding helps us implement algorithms, train models, and process large datasets efficiently. I discovered how loops, functions, and conditional statements are essential for building logic in programs. Beyond the basics, we also touched on concepts like supervised and unsupervised learning, where coding is used to train models to recognize patterns or make predictions. What fascinated me most was seeing how a few lines of code could enable machines to learn from data and improve performance over time. This class not only enhanced my technical skills but also sparked my curiosity to dive deeper into AI-driven problem solving.
